Parliament, Monday 03 June 2019 - The President of the Republic of South Africa Mr Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver his State of the Nation Address to a Joint Sitting of the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces. The State of the Nation Address is scheduled to take place in Parliament on Thursday, 20 June 2019
	
	This will be the first State of the Nation Address of the 6th term of Parliament following the national and provincial elections. The June State of the Nation Address will be delivered at 7 pm, as it has been the case in recent years.
	
	Media wishing to cover the State of the Nation Address from Parliament should apply for accreditation by no later than Wednesday, 5 June 2019 using the link provided here below:
	
	https://www.parliament.gov.za/media-accreditation/3
	
